parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping and Failure to Engage Gears
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage gears properly can cause the motorcycle to lose power, stall, or even crash, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The transmission slips out of gear
especially in second gear
when accelerating or decelerating; the motorcycle hesitates or stalls when shifting gears; the gears grind or make unusual noises when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the motorcycle to lose power, stall, or even crash, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The clutch shudders or vibrates violently when engaging first gear; the clutch grabs or releases abruptly; the clutch fails to engage or disengage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gearbox and shift fork failure can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The gearbox or shift fork fails
causing the transmission to slip out of gear or fail to engage gears properly; the gears grind or make unusual noises when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake rotor rivets can cause the rotor to become loose, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distance, and potentially, accidents.
symptoms: The rear brake rotor is loose
making noise when braking
vibrating when the pedal is applied
and allowing excessive lateral and rotational movement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch to engage can cause the bike to jerk or stutter, making it difficult to ride safely, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaking into the airbox or air filter can cause engine performance issues, decrease fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the left-hand side air filter
oil spraying down the side of the motorcycle
oil smell in the airbox.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Coolant leaks can cause engine overheating, damage to engine components, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: Coolant smell
coolant residue on engine components
empty overflow tank
coolant leaks from radiator cap or cooling system connecting hoses.
